013|title=Rocks Off: 50 Tracks That Tell the Story of the Rolling Stones|publisher=St. Martin's Press|location=New York|isbn=978-1-250-02631-6}}\n* {{cite book|last=McMillian|first=John|year=2013|title=Beatles vs. Stones|publisher=Simon & Schuster|location=New York|isbn=978-1-4391-5969-9}}\n* {{cite book|last=Miller|first=Jim|year=1980|title=The Rolling Stone Illustrated History of Rock & Roll: The Definitive History of the Most Important Artists and Their Music|publisher=Random House\n |location=New York |isbn=978-0-679-73728-5}}\n* {{cite book|last=Phelge|first=James|year=2000|title=Nankering with the Stones|isbn=978-1-55652-373-1}}\n* {{cite book|last=Sanchez|first=Tony|year=1996|title=Up and Down with the Rolling Stones|publisher=Da Capo |location=New York |isbn=978-0-306-80711-4|title-link=Up and Down with the Rolling Stones}}\n* {{cite book|last=Spitz|first=Marc|authorlink=Marc Spitz|year=2011|title=Jagger: Rebel, Rock Star, Rambler, Rogue|publisher=Gotham Books|isbn=978-1-59240-655-5|title-link=Jagger: Rebel, Rock Star, Rambler, Rogue}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|wikt=no|n=no|s=no|d=Q11036|mw=no|m=|species=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.rollingstones.com}}\n* {{Britannica|507167}}\n* {{Curlie|Arts/Music/Bands_and_Artists/R/Rolling_Stones/}}\n* {{Rockhall}}\n* {{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p5298|label=The Rolling Stones}}\n* {{Discogs artist|The Rolling Stones|The Rolling Stones}}\n* {{IMDb name|1213869}}\n* {{MusicBrainz artist|id=b071f9fa-14b0-4217-8e97-eb41da73f598|name=The Rolling Stones}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = The Rolling Stones\n|list =\n{{The Rolling Stones}}\n{{The Rolling Stones singles}}\n{{The Rolling Stones albums}}\n{{The Rolling Stones videos}}\n{{1989 Rock and Roll Hall of Fame}}\n{{Grammy Lifetime Achievement Award}}\n{{Michael Jackson Video Vanguard Award}}\n}}\n{{Mick Jagger}}\n{{Keith Richards}}\n{{Bill Wyman}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rolling Stones, The}}\n[[Category:The Rolling S